description.p:
By way of an exemplary example;



    

Enquiry: How many teenagers are within 100 meters of a Starbucks coffee shop?

Abstracted Response: 250 eighteen to fourteen males 369 eighteen to fourteen females are within 50 meters of a Starbucks coffee shop. 67% of this population has opted in for coupon and advertising communications from Starbucks

claim.claim-text:
1. A method, implemented by one or more computing devices configured with specific executable instructions, for managing information associated with a mobile device user, the method comprising:
receiving a query specifying criteria for identifying a set of mobile device users from a plurality of mobile device users;
determining, based at least in part on maintained mobile device user information, a subset of said plurality of mobile device users that satisfy the received criteria;
over a specified period of time, repeatedly determining a number of the identified determined subset of mobile device users who no longer satisfies the specified criteria; and
if the determined number is above a threshold number, providing an expiration notification reflecting the determined number of the identified determined subset of mobile device users who no longer satisfy the specified criteria.

7. A system for managing information associated with a mobile device user, the system comprising:
one or more computing devices configured to:
receive a query comprising criteria for identifying targeted mobile device users from a plurality of mobile device users;
determine a set of said plurality of mobile device users that satisfy the received criteria based at least in part on maintained mobile device user information;
after at least a specified amount of time, determine that at least a threshold number of said set of mobile device users no longer satisfy the criteria; and
provide an expiration notification indicative of said determination that at least a threshold number of said set of mobile device users no longer satisfy the criteria.
